column38: Little rain tonight but was only mostly spitting by the time we hit the streets at 6pm. Was trying to deal with a potential rape victim across from the McDonald's on 8th Street and she kept running away and trying to fight people as well another rather aggressive girl that was starting fights with everyone. We had to vacant the area due to violence and safety concerns. Called the non emerg line and gave the description of the female. We did two runs today and on our last run back ran into her by the superstore. Asked her again about what happened and she refused to talk to me and denied anything happening. Advised her that if this did happen and she would like to see someone or talk to someone Sheldon Chumir is our sexual assault hub in the city. She thanked me and moved on her way.
